Def:-The UPDATE statement is used to, modify the existing record in a table.
Synatx:-
UPDATE table_name
SET column1=value1, column2=value2..
WHERE condition;

Ex:-Single record updated.
UPDATE Customers
SET CustomerName='srinivas', City='Lakkavalli'
WHERE CustomerID = 1;

Ex2:-Multiple recorde updated.
UPDATE Customers
SET CustomerName = 'vanjakshi'
WHERE City = 'Chickmangalore';

Note:- Be careful when updating records. If you omit the WHERE clause, ALL records will be updated!
Ex:-
UPDATE Customers
SET CustomerName = 'Manjula';


